
[1]solicitude

   SOLIC'ITUDE, n. [L. solicitude.] Carefulness; concern; anxiety;
   uneasiness of mind occasioned by the fear of evil or the desire of
   good. A man feels soliciude when his friend is sick. We feel solicitude
   for the success of an enterprise. With what solicitude should men seek
   to secure future happiness.
